{
  "texts": [
    "The model predictors are based on our findings and other company information (Sect. 3.1.3).",
    "We first use as predictors the percentage of the top ten most disclosed ESG categories for each company.",
    "For example, if a company has ten percent of its generated triples concerning the ESG category Waste, and that is within its top ten most disclosed topics, the feature Category:Waste for this observation has a value of 0.1.",
    "We also consider the proportion of the E/S/G pillars based on all the disclosed categories for each company.",
    "In addition, we compute the category and action entropy for each company, indirectly representing the cardinality of the ESG categories and actions disclosed in its sustainability report (Sect. 3.5.2)."
  ]
}